name: J-Von Family Medical Centre-Not Walk-In Clinic

owner.name: J-Von Family Medical Centre-Not Walk-In Clinic (Owner)

address: J-Von Family Medical Centre-Not Walk-In Clinic, 4468 Beresford St., Burnaby, BC V5H 2Y8

detailed_reviews.review_text: Their doctors and staffs are very helpful and professional. The doctor prescribed me to do the ultrasound receptionist gave me the instruction how to book easily and faster. Once they received my report they called me and arranged me to see the doctor. Also they are so friendly and nice.

This clinic is conveniently located, just a few steps away from where we get off. The doctors are highly professional, quickly identifying the cause of the illness and providing appropriate treatment. They explained the diagnosis report in great detail. The receptionist at the front desk is polite and patient, helping us make appointments efficiently.

Doctors and staffs are extremely helpful and professional. The receptionists are always amazing. I m not familiar with their online booking system, they took their time, patiently and show me how to book it step by step. Doctors answer all my questions without rushing me out, and the wait wasn t too long. I always leave impressed.

J-Von Medical Clinic impressed me with their prompt response and efficient service. Upon receiving the lab results from my x-ray test, they quickly scheduled a follow-up doctor appointment. I really appreciate their extra care for me. Their commitment to promptness and attentive service is commendable.
My kid cried a lot due to flu shots. But the doctor and nurses are very patient and tried to comfort my kid. Also dr Chen sent my kid a sticker after the shot
Doctors are very nice and professional. My doc discovered my condition in time and treated me as quickly as possible.

The medical s online booking system is super convenient, and I no longer need to call in for booking appointments. This user-friendly feature has made managing healthcare appointments a breeze. I highly recommend it!

I received a follow-up call from the front desk to schedule a review of my lab reports, immediately after my results became available online. I am truly grateful for Dr. Zong and his exceptional front desk team, who have made me feel well-cared for
Friendly efficient receptionists, the doctors are patient and resourceful. Highly recommended.

I ve been here a number of times for various issues   the doctors are great, and the appointments do not feel rushed. The girls at the front do a great job given the very high volume. While in the waiting room I ve overhead them dealing with some very rude patients (I bet they don t act the same way when their coffee takes too long at Starbucks). I hope those patients realize there are systemic issues in the province and a shortage of GPs as there is not enough financial incentive to become a GP. The result is doctors and clinics being stretched thin and is no fault of the clinic itself.

Took my son there for his check-up recently, and he was super anxious about it. I thought he would freak out like when we were at his fluoride treatment, but surprisingly he was really into talking with the receptionists at the front. The ladies were super considerate and cheering to my son. They also gave him some stickers when we walked in, I thought that was really nice! Thank you ladies for making our visit easy and smooth!

Orignally, I gave give Five stars to Dr. Gill for his patience, persistence and general helpful, caring attitude. I still recommend him as a doctor, but my frustration is with his Front Counter Receptionists as I had a missed call from J-Von Medical, but a patient cannot return a call or email them (I tried several times, unsuccessfully)!  In the past, Ive been able to book online and speak with Dr. GILL. However, even though I am an Existing patient, the on-line system wont accept my email (same one I have had for 20 years!) I had to contact Vancouver General Hospital to try and get a message to my Doctor...who I have not heard back from in weeks! I was sent the email by the Doctor to get in touch with this medical clinic, yet it is the very same email that I have received messages  directly from J-Von Medical that states: Do Not email to this address as messages will Not be answered!

I ve been in this clinic with Dr. Zong , for few years, it s been a good experience with Dr and receptionists , I know they are very very  busy and they have to deal with so many things specialist people with bad manners, I was there once with my new born baby a guy was screaming at them and he didn t even was a patient of this clinic he was a husband of a patient, which I felt very sorry for the ladies at front desk . I wish they can extend their phone line so we can call anytime at the day as before .
Dr. Liu is super nice and professional. The receptionists are also efficient and helping.

Excellent doctors at this clinic. Dr. Zong goes above and beyond for his patients! The medical office assistants recently gave me a call to book for check up in person appointment was very efficient. With added booking online for virtual appointments made it easier for me have more regular doctor check ups as I am not required to wait long walk in times. And when I did have to go into the clinic I felt exceptional safe with all the Covid protocol the office had. Only complain I had was that during my short visit there, some possible wait in patients did try to barge in while being very rude to the office assistants. Its not something that clinic have control over, but during pandemic time, its truly sad that people are not more understanding of protocols.

i ve been a patient at jvon for a few years and this is a great clinic with great doctors. the doctors here have always helped assess my medical issues. the front desk are always helpful and patient whenever i have additional questions

I saw Dr. Nguyen here for probably 2.5 years. The staff was always very helpful and polite. I made online appointments and never waited more than 4 minutes - there was generally good availability to book appointments. Ive just transferred to someone much closer to my house and everyone helped so much to make that a smooth transition.
I had a bad experience with Customer Service and Doctors; If you want to waste time and be treated like nobody else go visit them and in the end you will be frustrated
They helped me make a CT appointment and called me to remind. So nice

Once you walk in, you know you are in good hands. Although many people on here complain about the receptionists (yes, I think they need some more training in telephone communication, manners, courtesy, etiquette, etc.), I do think that this clinic is super efficient in my personal experience. Let me give you a few examples: 1) While the clinic my cousin goes to regularly refused to refer him  to a gastroenterologist, J-Von did it timely and soon he had the endoscopy and colonoscopy done; 2) While the clinic my cousin goes to never called him after receiving the endoscopy and colonoscopy results, J-Von called as soon as they received the fax and booked him immediately for a follow-up to give him peace of mind; 3) After J-Von prescribed my mother a new drug, J-Von called us a few days later for a follow-up. Besides, Dr. Zong, a young doctor, has up-to-date knowledge and is English-Mandarin bilingual. I want to ask you: How many clinics would go that far to do these? None! If you had an unpleasant experience here and if it is all trivia (like with the receptionists, etc.), come on, have some patience and give it more time! It cant be wrong.

I had my first appointment today,  Joyce did teeth cleaning for me.  She is very patient and detail-oriented,  did an awesome job. Howard Liu is also very friendly and helpful, without being pushy about making my next appointment.  They even tried to ask my previous dental office for my x-ray so that they can save money for me!  Awesome experience!
thank you jvon for your best service! The front staff explained my dad the requisition which he really appreciates it! He cannot English so he let me say something. Best clinic ever

First off, I have to say I dont usually rate medical/dental clinics. After all, I dont go around town trying different clinics. If I dont like one, I just dont go there anymore. And if I find one thats satisfactory, I will stay there. Im guessing most people are like me. And once in a while (if youre lucky) you will come across a clinic that goes above and beyond your expected level of service and knowledgeable staff. Such is the case with J-VON Medical and Dental. They have set a new standard of what customer service should be. They also have a very well trained team of medical experts and dental professionals. The first time I walked in I was greeted with a friendly smile by the super helpful reception team. They were able to book an appointment time that worked for me, given my busy schedule. And when I came in for my appointment they recognized me and greeted me by my name. How awesome is that? It really felt like a warm personal welcome. The clinics are always clean, and the place looks so modern. All the equipment there looks new and the technology used in some of these are pretty slick. The dentist who was assigned to me was named Howard. I cant say enough of his professionalism and respect. He works with his patients to ensure they have all the information to make the best decision with regards to the treatment plan or procedure. I highly recommend this medical/dental clinic because of the friendly knowledgeable staff, exceptional service, and highly trained professionals. And on top of that, they are so conveniently located next to Metrotown Station and super clean and modern.

I have been seeing Dr. Zhai for several times this year. She understood me very well. She is very professional,  responsible , and patient.  After getting the reports, she also gave me suggestions about diet and life styles. She is very helpful. I really appreciate her.

I am a Chinese and I speak Cantonese. My family doctor is Dr Cheung. When I need an appointment, their staff always try to help me getting an appointment. I am a patient with multiple medical conditions; they will call me if my tests are abnormal and follow up with me. staff are super friendly. They also offer virtual appointment with Dr. during COVID pandemic. They are helpful and professional, Great clinic!
Doctor is so patiently. The place is very convenient for me.
Dr. Qiming Wu is one if the best family Doctor. He is very knowledgeable and very patient, my parents are lucky to meet him.

Very nice staffs and excellent precaution for COVID.  I feel very safe when I visit here each time. Dr Zhai is amazing. She is so professional, empathtic and just a warm person. She listens actively. She gives a sufficient amount of relative information that I need and always offers options for me to choose, which makes me feel my rights and choices are respected. I feel very comfortable working with Dr. Zhai, Yun Lei, highly recommended! staff and excellent

I had some misunderstandings with the lady before. And now we already have a talk face to face. The front desk lady was patiently explained to me.  I am now fully understand how much work theyve been putting in their jobs.  It is a very good clinic and people who came to their clinic so far, have a pleasure time with staff.  :) Thank You

Candy Cheung is a very good doctor. She is straight forward telling you what is your problem even you may not like to hear, but this is what a good doctor should do. We need someone like her to tell us the truth about our health. Thank you Doctor Candy Cheung.
I couldn t get a X-ray appointment time asap, so I called them for help. They were so nice to get an appointment for me. I appreciated that

I came this place for Family doctor and dental cleaning. Cindy is my family doctor and she was really patient to all my questions and gave useful suggestions. Joyce did a really good job on my dental cleaning and they waived my cleaning expense since I did the x-ray. They even gave me a liquid flosser for new patient gift. The most impressive thing for the dental clinic is, they mount a TV on the ceiling to allow patients watch TV while lying on the bed.
I am lucky to get a spot in and now they donot accept walk in anymore. The service is good, and doctors are amazing. Staff is fantastic.
Even though my appointment was really delayed. I was initially really upset but I appreciate that they were understanding and empathetic and reached out to apologize. They seem genuine to me!

I wrote them bad reviews before because my appointments always delayed but I changed it . My husband s report was taken care by their staff professionally and they helped him to order it very fast. We appreciate their help.

Excellent service. I tried to book an in person appointment via phone and they were able to fill me in the next day.  The consultant with Dr. Gill was very thorough. The clinic is modernly cleaned as well

I highly recommend this clinic. I had serious headache couple months ago and visited here. The receptionist was nice and pretty quick responding to my request and questions. Dr Lau gave me a checkup carefully and listened to my concerns. I was referred to a neurologist and waiting for further examination. BWT, I had wisdom tooth removal last week and dentist is friendly too.

I love J-Von medical clinic, and I am royal patient of this clinic. I would definitely give a 5 STAR. I saw almost every doctor in the clinic, and the doctors and receptionists all very polite and helpful. I regularly visit this office because I have to review my INR result every week. I feel like a home while I am in the office.   I saw a few unpleasant patients. When they could not get what they want, so they went to the internet and wrote something not nice. I had been visiting a few clinics in my life, and I think J-Von medical is the best. I would strongly recommend going there and check up.
Dr. GILL is wonderful and I am very lucky to have him. The reception staff have also always been great, helpful and very friendly.
I have been to the clinic more than 2 years. My family all see dr lau and we satisfy  clinic services. The receptionists are amazing people.

very thank you to Dr.zong for seeing my mom today. my mom came to Canada for a visit, she is over 80 years old and every time when my mom is sick or uncomfortable, she  always go and see Dr.zong at j-von .medical. Dr.Zong is very nice, patient and responsible. he is very professional and has really good integrity. Dr.zong always thinks about the patient and puts curing the patient in priority. Praise for his character and medical ethics. Also, j-von medicals receptionists has really good service, are kind and nice.

Good clinic, professional clinic! These people who wrote the mean reviewing. Can you show your real names?  please! Like who is : Dan D, Ana.L, Onecouver, smashing, Minsi C. and V V and Z Z. is it even a real name?  You keep saying never coming back but do you? like the one called smashing, look at you, and like to destroy the world I guess. You are not good people!  I can tell the clinic if you show your real names I can report to them who you really are. I understand people may have a bad day, but keep your postings professional. Some of days, they can be slow, and some of the bad reviews I understand because of the timing or other things may not be perfect. I understand the other reviews, But for  Dan D, Ana.L, Onecouver, smashing, Minsi C. and V V and Z Z. You are a joke!  First, you are mean people and you have a bad life. Your life is a mass so you like to complain. Second, you still want to come back and use their resources because they are nice and you just cannot keep your mouth shut. You are not happy, just because of that, your lips have to move and fingers have to type to let your anger out. Third, you are not brave, you worried because people like me maybe reporting you to the clinic so you never can take advantage of this clinics convenient location. I am their neighbor and I go to their clinic since day one. I am a housewife and I appreciate this clinics professionalism. Donot be mean and post things not even truthful. I am not planning to go any clinics only to this one!
Polite and responsible reception, would have missed my appointment if she didn t remind me a day ahead!

I saw Dr Zong here and had very positive experience, all stuff is helpful and nice. Also they are willing to helpful provide information if you need to make a claim for insurance if MSP not valid. Dr Zong is good doctor and refer me to specialist with my different issues. I will recommend J-Von medical!!
Dr Zong is my family doctor, and he has been doing very well on his job and helped me a lots. Thank you Dr Zong
Overall it is a good clinic.I usually go there only for pills or yearly blood test so my experience is always positive. I was coughing last year and they did exam me throughly.

I got a whiplash, and Winnie, Edris, Jason have done an amazing job to relax then strengthen my muscles. Jason is really good at vertigo and hes so caring. Edris is so good at massage I always fell asleep during session. Thanks guy for helping me out.
Clinic has amazing staff. I came in and want to book appointments. They showed me step by step.
I have been going to this clinic for a few years. I was recently helped by Dr. Yunlei Zhai and she is an excellent doctor. I was very impressed by her knowledge, follow-up and professionalism.

Thank you so much J-Von medical center for the best customer service experience .. I was afraid of dentists for a long time but the dentist I had was very smooth and he waited me to calm patiently.. All stuff were so friendly,so I changed my family doctor to its clinic as well..I am so thankful them to be in such a convenient location and take care of people in a good manners.
I feel extremely safe to go this clinic during covid 19. They separate the people and the doctors are so helpful. Dr Gill is a good doctor.
My two years old got stickers from the clinic. What I see from them is they are trying to make my child feel comfortable to see doctors. I appreciate it.
I book appointment and I wait for 20 minutes. So? I have waited the clinic near to them for 2 hours! I feel lucky to find a place like here. I enjoy coming here.
I really like this clinic. Good location, meter parking in front of clinic. Dr Julia saw me and she is nice. People working in the front is friendly.
I was so lucky to have a family doctor here. No matter doctors or staff there are so helpful  .
The reception lady was able to get me an same day appointment. Awesome service!
Doctors speak Chinese. Many of them speaks the language and I feel I can address my concern. I like the doctors here. Never had any problems.
Excellent service. They are still accepting new patients.
They taught me how to book online with Dr Lau.That s so nice!
So happy I have a family doctor here. They are all so nice
They called me to remind my specialist appointment. That s so warm
I always receive calls from them and seems like they really care about my health. I have been treating well by doctors and staff
I never had a such great experience in a medical clinic except here.  The office is clean and neat and their staff are very friendly and helpful.
one of the best walk in in burnaby! Now they are getting busier because people recognize their service. Many people coming here and I hope they can be less busier now.
Great service. I was recently helped by Dr. Gill for my herniated disc over virtual appointments and he s been very thorough.
So clean clinic and especially staff and doctors speak mandarin. So appreciate
I will come back to this clinic again and today I saw a female doctor. My English is ok and they have many Chinese doctors so I donot need to worry some medical terminology.
We would love to dr liu to accept all our family!
Courteous  and polite staff. Dr. Zong is patient, professional and addresses all patients concerns in detail. Highly recommend this place.
Good clinic: staff is helpful and always smiles. Clinic is clean, would like to come back again!
This has to be one of the cleanest places Ive ever been.  Staff were friendly and professional.  Its located next to Metrotown, which is really convenient to get to.
doctors are quite nice and helpful. I saw Dr lau, dr Cheung and dr zhai and have great experiences
Wonderful staff and great doctors. An easy location to get to on transit, if youre driving parking can be a bit tricky.
would love to come back and I saw dr zhai as a walk in patient today and she is fantastic!
I came in to see my blood test and I saw dr Tuet. She is very nice and their staff also friendly.
Girls in the front are so busy all the time, but still helped me and answered my questions. I really appreciated that
Staff is polite, period! I get my birth control pills in here. Nothing to complain.
Clinic has amazing staff. They helped to guide where go to lifelab.
Dr. Zong very knowledge and got back to me in a timely manner after my exam.
Could not be happier to find this clinic! I like Dr Lau! Also their staff is not rude.
Great experience The receptionist and Dr zhai are very patient
It is the clinic I always recommended it. I live close and like their service. Friendly staff
Doctors and receptionists are super professional and responsible
Nice clinic, friendly staff and always responsive.
The staff are all very friendly, and I love being able to book appointments online.
excellent services friendly receptionist, nice doctor :)
walked in at 8:40am. staff processed me, saw dr nguyen, she fixed me up in 5 minutes. walked out at 8:55am
All good
service is good. I met Dr. Zong very good doctor and their staff are good staff.
My parents are patients of dr Candy. We like this location also nicest staff.

Always helpful and able to get me in, very hands-on, unbiased and investigates things all the way through.
Always take care of my family and friends

name: Kamo Bakery

owner.name: Kamo Bakery (Owner)

address: Kamo Bakery, Privet Parking Available in the back of store, 5552 Victoria Dr, Vancouver, BC V5P 3W1

detailed_reviews.review_text: Our cousins recommended this bakery and we went there soon afterward. The friendly owner greeted us and gave us samples to try. We ended up getting 5 different types of pastries. We definitely will return and get all other items.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Were over the moon to receive your five-star rating! Thank you for sharing your positive experience with us. Your support means the world to us, and were excited to have the opportunity to continue exceeding your expectations in the future.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Been curious about this bakery for quite some time now and I took the chance to pass by after doing my errands this afternoon - AND IM GLAD I DID! I got to meet the owner, Kamo himself. Such a nice guy! He immediately knew that it was my first time and he gave a me a piece of their Baklava for free AND I LOVED IT! It was my first time and Ive only seen baklavas on TV.   It was so good! Ive had my eyes fixed on their pistachio cookies and bought a couple to take home. It was indeed a positive experience for me! Ill definitely be back to try the rest of their selections! If I could give 6 stars here, I would! EDIT: Added pictures on the review
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks so much for giving us your take on how we are doing. Were glad that customers like you are having a great experience at Kamo bakery.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Went for the first time and the owner was SUPER friendly and sweet! He let gave us multiple free samples so we could see what he liked, and everything tasted amazing!! The paklava was super crispy and full of flavor. Highly recommend this bakery
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: On behalf us all of us at Kamo Bakery, I would like to thank you for sharing this great review about Kamo bakery products ! We are thrilled that you enjoyed your experience.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Pros: Extremely friendly staff. Very welcoming and helpful. Sweet items have a great balanced mixture of nuts and pastry. The taste of nuts in their items is very prevalent, and not overshadowed by sweetness. Suitable for usual Asian tastes. Additional area with difficult to find pantry items. Cash and credit/debit cards accepted. Accessible by public transit. Parking available in the back of the bakery. Cons: Mostly for pick up. No seating area. *** Can t wait to try their breads and savoury items.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks so much for giving us your take on how we are doing. Were glad that customers like you are having a great experience at Kamo bakery

detailed_reviews.review_text: Professional, friendly atmosphere. Checked the place for the first time yesterday and met the owner. Very generous and friendly person. I have tried some baklava, kenafa and pastry with dates. It is delicious, lightly sweetened as I prefer. There a variety of flavours and options to choose from. I had a mix box. In addition, the bread is fresh and tasty. It will go well with cheese either breakfast or dinner. My taste buds asked for more!! Highly recommended to try Kamo Bakery!!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: On behalf us all of us at Kamo Bakery, I would like to thank you for sharing this great review about Kamo bakery products ! We are thrilled that you enjoyed your experience.

detailed_reviews.review_text: The best baclava in the city hands down. My favourite bakery to get these delectable treats! Even my Vietnamese mom who s the pickiest eater in the world loves them. The royal baklavas are pricier but the artistry is worth it if you re aiming to impress. The pistachio and walnut baklavas taste just as good though! The pistachio cookies are also delicious. They also have parking in the back.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello Angela, Thank you for taking the time to leave a 5-star review of Kamo Bakery! Your feedback is incredibly valuable to us, and were overjoyed to learn that you had such a positive experience at our establishment. We are dedicated to creating a warm and inviting environment for our customers, and were thrilled that we were able to make your visit enjoyable. We cant wait to have the opportunity to serve you again, and if theres anything we can do to make your next visit even better, please dont hesitate to let us know.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Best baklava Ive ever had - Kamo Bakery doesnt soak their baklava in syrup so it stays light, crisp and not too sweet and is filled with good quality nuts. Also dont sleep on the pistachio cookies - they taste like pistachio Nutella and melt in your mouth when consumed with your choice of milk. The owner is also super friendly, happy to explain what the different types of baklava are and proud of his baked goods. Definitely makes me happy to support and glad theyre not too far away so I can drop by a sweet treat.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: We truly appreciate your continuous support and trust in us. Your 5-star review brightens our day and serves as a constant reminder of why we love what we do. We ll continue striving to provide exceptional products, services and outstanding customer care to make every interaction with us remarkable.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Ordered in Uber Eats, wanted to get 1lb of mixed baklava so called to ask if that is possible to do so as Uber didn t show 50/50 option. Super nice and friendly man (thank You!!) said he can make a box of mixed baklava, and that he will also put a small gift to try - Royal Paklava - it was soooo good, a lot of flavourful filling, not too sweet, it is PERFECT Walnut & Pistachio Baklavas also well balanced in flavors and structure, the top is perfectly crispy, great filling, soft inside, sweetness level is perfect for me (most baklavas I tried in Vancouver before were super sweet and had less filling so couldn t even notice nuts flavour). Definitely recommend to try! :)
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello Anastasia! Thank you for the fantastic review! We put a lot of effort into making our products. The Royal Paklava is new product we just made it, so we are thrilled to hear that you are enjoying it.

detailed_reviews.review_text: We are from a different city and found this hidden gem while waiting to meet up with family. The owner is so super sweet! Because it was our first time there, he gave us a Paklava to try. For my partner who never had one before, he said it was love at first taste. The Paklava isnt super sweet or super greasy like some Ive had before.  I highly recommend going  if youve never tried or if youre visiting Vancouver. We know this is the one place well go everytime we visit.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: On behalf us all of us at Kamo Bakery, I would like to thank you for sharing this great review about our store! We are thrilled that you enjoyed your experience.

detailed_reviews.review_text: I thought i didn t really like baklava until i tried it here. So delicious! We bought a pound as soon as we tried one. The owner was really friendly and helpful too! Will go back 100%
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: ank you so much for the 5-star review! We are thrilled to hear that you are enjoying our product&service and appreciate your feedback. Keep it coming!

detailed_reviews.review_text: My son and I went to this lovely Kurdish bakery after hearing the rave reviews from a friend. Their baklava is phenomenal. The best Ive ever had. Less sweet than other recipes. Everything was very fresh and made from high quality ingredients. The owner and employees are very warm and welcoming, so this is a very easy 5 stars! We will definitely be back.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for the 5-star review. The team at Kamo Bakery  is thrilled you re happy with your recent store visit.

detailed_reviews.review_text: This is the best Middle Eastern bakery in Vancouver. Very delicious and authentic. Their baklava and klachia are not that sweet. Very consistent taste and so fresh. Friendly customer service. I highly recommend this bakery.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for sharing your experience.

detailed_reviews.review_text: The best baklava I ever had.  Love the pistachio one!  Its not too sweet - just sweet enough and flaky with a beautiful buttery flavor.  I find baklavas at other places too sweet but the ones here are perfect.  Very friendly and welcoming owner.  Pay by weight and I find it very affordable.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: On behalf us all of us at Kamo Bakery, I would like to thank you for sharing this great review about Kamo bakery products ! We are thrilled that you enjoyed your experience.

detailed_reviews.review_text: I discovered Kamo bakery while I was walking to an appointment. I immediately walked in to check it out. The man at the counter was very helpful and kind. Ive had Baklava before and they sell something similar called, Paklava. I was hesitant to try it because the baklava I had was sticky, chewy and way too sweet. He said, ours is different. Im so glad I tried it. It was absolutely delicious. It was crispy, buttery and not cloyingly sweet. Delicious!!! I ended up buying 6 pieces that day. They also had pomegranate molasses. I bought a bottle of that too. I cant wait until they have Knafeh. He said they will have it soon. EDIT: I went to this bakery again and the service is consistently friendly and welcoming. I love their Walnut Paklava. I bought a pound of it this time. I am also in love with their breads and orange cookies.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for taking the time to share your experience at Kamo Bakery. We take pride in knowing our customers are happy with their store experience.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Truly the best paklava I have ever had! Owner was incredibly kind and really passionate about his products. I can t recommend this place enough. Everything was not too sweet, and just the right balance of flavour and crispiness. I will absolutely be returning!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: On behalf us all of us at Kamo Bakery, I would like to thank you for sharing this great review about Kamo bakery products ! We are thrilled that you enjoyed your experience.

detailed_reviews.review_text: The best baklava i ve ever had!! Top quality and the bakery owners are Angels   the food exudes Love.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for taking the time to leave a 5-star review. Your feedback is greatly appreciated.

detailed_reviews.review_text: I just visited this place and I gotta say it s a hidden gem! I got to try their baklavas very tasty and fresh, not super sweet. Their collection of breads is very interesting, I got the Samoon bread, so excited to try it. I spoke with a very friendly guy and got to try their baklavas! I m very excited to try these UPDATED REVIEW: Keep coming back for their specialty breads! They are so good for quick breakfast and you can stuff them easily with anything you want!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Everything the other review says are right! The owner is definitely the sweetest thing in the shop as all their pastries are made with low sugar. After hearing its my first time there, the owner was so enthusiastic to introduce to me what they have and giving me a couple of samples to try. It was a very heart warming gesture. First the baklavas, the sweetness is only about 1/2 or less than the other baklavas out there, I can finally taste the true taste of the baklavas without filling my mouth with syrup. My husband absolutely loves it. My absolute favorites in the shop is the sesame cake and the dates pastry. Sesame cake tastes really fragrant and addictive. You dont get sick and tired of the taste at all. The texture is more like a cookie. The date pastry is quite different from the other places Ive tried and definitely my second choice from the shop. The orange chocolate cookie is another must have if you are a chocolate person. Its got such a strong dark bitter chocolate taste to it youll feel like youre eating dark chocolate itself. The texture was also really good. It has a combination of cookies and brownies texture making it nice and moist but still crunchy. Everything is priced by weight (baklava costs more). I think on average, each pc will cost around $1. This place is a bit out of my way, but with this quality, Im ok to make a trip there more often now

detailed_reviews.review_text: We promised to write a review when we visited, so here it is. We had seen the sign up for several months and were curious to know what would be opening in this unprepossessing space on the drive. We happened to walk by the other day and they were open, so we ventured in. Its a tiny bakery run by some lovely and friendly Syrians, with a selection of fresh Syrian breads and baklava. We asked some questions, which were answered enthusuastically and we bought a bag of their freshly baked flatbreads (Samoon) and an assortment of their pastries. They also gave us a small bag of bonus bread. It was their opening day, which can sometimes mean things go wrong. Not here! The flatbreads were great. Light and airy - perfect with falafels or charcuterie - whatever you like. The star of the show, however, is the pastries. The baklava is light, crisp, fresh and not too sweet or drowned in syrup, which is all too common, especially at Persian bakeries. There were also the most delicious sesame squares and date pastries. Try them all - nothing was disappointing. If they keep this standard up, they deserve to be very successful. They have opened in a difficult spot, but they deserve support and we will return there next time we are on Victoria Drive. Grab some pastries and have them with some good coffee. Heaven!

We loved them so much the next day my husband ordered some to bring to work to share. Everybody loved them. The baklavas are so spectacular I almost forgot to mention their other sweets and the owner. The owner--Ive got to ask for his name next time--is super nice. As a first timer in the bakery, he offered to let us try anything were interested. We ended up trying almost everything and buying a whole bunch of different sweets. In total we got 12 baklavas and a small box of assorted cookies. We finished them in 3 days, just the two of us! They are lethal because you dont feel guilty eating them at all. Its a joy to discover small neighbourhood gems like Kamo. It makes you appreciate the little things in life that much more.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Recommended to try this place! The dessert tastes amazing. I m not a big fan of sugary sweets, and Minus Cake got the sweetness right!   The cake is fluffy with a creamy mousse texture that melts in the mouth.
Totally recommended. Last year they prepared my babys 1 year old cake. They are very helpful and accommodating. Food

I really liked. A nice little place. The service is excellent and we tasted very good desserts. The desserts are not too sweet, they are just right. A varied choice: some combinations are available (bubble cake and drink) but you can also make your own combination. I tried number 7 and the mix of flavors was well thought out!  I would like to go back to try other flavors.

I got the Rose Oolong Peach Cake + Honeycomb Dalgona Latte and my friend got the Vanilla Strawberry Shortcake + Iced Shaken Lychee Black Tea. I would highly recommend the rose peach cake as its something I havent been able to get anywhere else and it tasted divine! The rest was sweet and tasted exactly as expected, especially the strawberry cake and the lychee black tea. Not to make that sound bad, theyre staples in every store for a reason (they never miss)!! Though, not going to lie, wasnt a huge fan of the honeycomb in my dalgona latte as it was too sweet and it was slightly unnerving every time Id encounter its crunchy texture. Still drank it all, but probably wouldnt get it again... Other than that, the decor was nice and clean and the atmosphere was quiet and serene. Also, its a little on the expensive side... so definitely more of an experience than a regular hang-out spot. Hope the employees enjoyed the relaxing morning as it seemed like a slow shift (to be fair we went around brunch time on a Tuesday). Tldr, worth it to try the rose oolong peach cake and experience the fun of the stacking cake cups.
This is so goooooooooood omg! Both combos were delicious and the girl who works at the place is very sweet and helpful. Totally would come again to try all the other combos.
I have to say, the idea of dessert with a bubble tea was just a thought. Now Ive found the real deal. So far I am looking forward to come back and try more of it

Stumbled across this gem on social media and knew we had to try! Wow it did not disappoint!   The cake bubble was seriously the best treat I have had in ages!  So many options to pick from.  Bold strong flavors, creamy moose. The drink was fresh with no artificial flavor. We will be back again!  Just wish they opened sooner!!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for coming by Brittaney! Have a great day!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Visited this place with my wife on labour day. Nice little shop with cute interior decoration. Service was good. We were a bit confused to see the menu but the staff was explained to us very patiently. Friendly space to hang out with friends and family. Price is reasonable since can enjoy bubble tea and cake at the same time. After tasting the combo we both enjoyed their preset combination. Very unique, creative and aesthetic cup design. The peach cake is my favourite one and they sold out around 3pm today, Im glad to got it. I even ate too fast before I realized to take a picture! Rum cake can taste real rum flavour inside. They hide some raisin inside the cake to bring out the whole texture. Drinks used simple ingredients but very refreshing. I saw they were washing and cut fruits for preparation. I love to see business to use fresh ingredients to highlight their standard in food industry. Very pleasing experience for afternoon snack, will definitely go back again with our children to try their other products!
So fun and delicious!! I love that you can mix and match the drinks and cake. My fav so far is the tiramisu cake with the brown sugar milk tea
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for coming by! Have a great day!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Ordered combo #5. The matcha latte (I asked them to switch corn milk with regular milk for my drink) was very tasty. The cake went perfectly with the drink. Now I understand why they make these two items a combo. I especially love the decorations in the shop. The two ladies at the front desk were very friendly. The containers they used are different from usual bobble tea shop. I can tell they put lot of efforts on everything. More on the pricy side, but worth trying!

Really cute place selling both cold tea and CAKE--all in delicious and unique flavours. Came here yesterday and they were very organized and systematic with Covid rules in place. I got the earl grey cake which was very creamy and not too sweet. I also got the honeycomb dalgona latte and  recommend swirling the foam with milk thoroughly before drinking.
Good combination, dessert and drink, right amount of sweetness. Cute little place. Several options to choose.

Great desserts that were much more then I was expecting. The cake and the drink pairing is such a neat idea, I will definitely be back to try another. I got the seasonal coconut taro ube cake with the mango sago coconut slush. The cake was not too sweet and a perfect light summer cake. The slush paired well as it was not too sweet. My friend and I both got drinks and found them less sweet then we were expecting. For me, I found this a pleasant surprise, but she got a matcha drink and didnt like it as much. So, if you are expecting or wanting a bubble tea level of sweetness, might want to check with the staff about which drinks are sweet. The service was quick (much quicker than bubble tea usually) and I would love to come back and try more flavour combos.

Love the cake+drink combo concept! You can easily devour the delectable   and immediately go for a sip of the  , rinse and repeat   Wonder if someone patented that design because it s just genius and perfect for devouring on the run Had the  cake + lychee iced tea combo with zero sugar and boy this combo was super yum! Cake was sweetened just right and took me back to my childhood when I gorged on Melona treats, but this was better! The Lychee tea had really refreshing fruit bits, this combo is solid! Also tried the   raspberry   cake + hawthorn dates refresher with zero sugar and this was fab too. Now here s my 2 cents on the pricing of the 2 dessert combo - it s pretty fair y all! First we typically pay $7 for a decent cake anyway and also another $7 for a good quality non powdered bbt (you know what I m talking about) and this place is a one-stop shop for you to address your need for a little something nice and sweet. Would I come back again, you bet!

The staff, location, desserts, and atmosphere are so worth it! A unique treat. A mouse like cake of your choice with a yummy drink. Id recommend it for a date night idea, a unique treat, a birthday adventure. And the staff were very friendly to boot!
The fresh mango passion fruit combo was great, but I think the cup design is a bit odd because the straw is kinda stuck and can t stir the drink because of the top round cup.

Perfection each time! I trust no one else to make my cakes. The whole process is done by email, turnaround is quick and professional. I love that they offer delivery and for the quality, the prices are comparable. Thank you Minus!!!

I live in Calgary and wanted to get something as a surprise for my close friend who lives in Vancouver. Found this little bubble tea bake shop online and they exceeded my expectations. They went above and beyond in terms of my delivery and cake request. My friend absolutely loved it. Definitely recommend this place for being so accommodating and sweet. Phenomenal food and service. Thanks so much again!

I m not sure if it s a drink place or a dessert place, but who cares! You can have your cake/bbt and eat it too! Decor is adorable. Cuddle cakes are so soft and delicate, not too sweet, and so delicious. Dessert cups a little on the pricy side, drink + dessert cup = $13-14
Amazing   really good drinks and desserts, fast service and friendly staff - interior is really cute too :)

Very innovative desserts and drinks here. Definitely unique and never seen before. They combine a cake and a drink which you can eat and drink with one hand, perfect for on the go. Not too sweet, seems they tailored it just nicely. Friendly owner, very helpful staff. Street parking is a bit limited. Left: blackcurrant rum raisin cake with lychee slush Mid: chocolate cake with Oreo slush Right: Earl Grey cake with dalgona latte *Edit: owner told me there is more street parking around the side, and a larger parking lot behind their building! Now it is even easier to visit!

We went last week for walk in but realized they don t open for walk in anymore. Everything pre order only. We are their returned customer so didn t check google before we went there. Luckily meet the owner, she let us know she becomes newly mom this year and she wants to make sure cakes made with freshly everyday so she has to make this difficult decision. No maternity leave is cruel for a mom, and she has to take care of her baby plus working everyday. Please be nice to small business owners, they are trying to make things better!!!!

Amazing cakes and drinks! We go every week :) the cake/ drink combo are very cute very IG-able! Delicious cakes. Our fav are chocolate, chocolate caramel, green tea yuzu, and strawberry. Yummy, dif textures inside, not too sweet.  Drinks are very yummy too!! Matcha latte has got loads of matcha powder! Jasmine tea with pearls and milk foam is nice too I like it that this particular tea is unsweetened I think..
One of the best dessert place. Wonderful drinks and all kinds of seasonal cakes. My favorite place.
Gorgeous, delicious, light and not too sweet. So happy. Thank you so much for such a beautiful cake!

Late Review We have ordered from Minus Cake Boutique for many festive occasions and our favourite cake is the Jasmine Pearl Lava Cake. It is very creamy with subtle salty and sweet caramelized filling. Unfortunately when I bought the 8inch cake for my mothers birthday November 27, 2021, we discovered the cream in the centre was sour- like sour cream. This made the entire cake taste weird and off-putting . We called the next morning to ask the baker if they knew what happened, although they were not sure and had some hypothesis (maybe they forgot to thin out the cream with fresh cream?) Minus Cake Boutique took ownership of their product and offered to refund (if we bring the cake back) or make a replacement cake. I purchased many times from Minus and a refund was not what I was looking for. I simply wanted to inform them about the quality of their item. There was no way my family could eat another whole  8inch cake (we hate wastage and were determined to carve the sour cream part out of the first cake and make do with what we had) so I suggested making a smaller 6inch one so that we could taste what the cake should taste like. Minus Cake Boutique delivered and we picked up the remade cake and I am grateful and super happy to say, it tasted just the way we remembered it to be. Thank you very much for coming through with excellent customer service. We are very happy and will continue to buy your specialty cakes in the future. Already eyeing another cake for our next festive celebration.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello Sigman, Thank you so much for allowing us the chance to rectify this quality issue. We appreciate your patronage to date and look forward to serving you more!

Doc said it d take 6-12 weeks, but I played my first golf 5 weeks after injury and I played better because I was more stronger in my core and glutes. I m still getting treatments b c of sore left shoulder & back and she s used shock therapy for shoulder and it has rapidly helped the shoulder. My back pain is also getting better. 6 weeks later now, I m playing golf better & I can run if I have to, btw, I m a newish senior. detailed_reviews.review_text: As an Indian Classical musician, I have been tirelessly working through sitting cross legged and playing my tabla for over 10 hours a day for 30 + years. Needless to say, both Professional Hazard and age has caught up to me and I need intense physiotherapy for my neck, shoulders, arms, hips and legs. Basically, a full overhaul of my joints, ligaments and muscles. I came to see my dear friend Krishna Jeeja at her MJ Physio clinic on Fraser St and 41st in Vancouver and started my treatment. I was quite nervous as asides from the few massages I have had with my wife at couples spas I have never been to any sort of therapy in this regard. Krishna completely made me feel at ease, explaining to me the details of my therapy and what was required. She made correct analysis on all of my problem joints in my body and exactly described my pain as if it was me talking. She is very knowledgeable on the workings of the human body. I feel an intense decrease in pain ever since Krishna started treating me, as a matter of fact I feel much better now than I have in years though I am aware it will take more than a few sessions to correct my body alignment. As I have been having intense pain in my ankle bones as well as my shoulders and neck Krishna was very quick in identifying the problem as bursitis. I assumed that only cortisol can treat this pain but I was hesitant of ever getting that treatment done. After Krishna told me they treat bursitis through laser  I am looking forward to getting laser treatment done in their Surrey location. I will recommend this place to anyone in need of physio. Krishna is kind hearted, professional, direct and an absolute joy to talk to. She is friendly and makes you feel at ease. Their facility has a nice gym, state of the art equipment and a very friendly receptionist. For the first time in my life I feel that I will get better and continue my work in music. Thank you Krishna and thank you MJ Physio for being there- and thank you for supporting the Arts in our city ( MJ Physio is one of our major sponsors for our Mushtari Begum Festival of Indian Classical Music and Dance) and selflessly donating your time to our Vancouver community. I give you 6/5 stars!

He is very well spoken , confident , handsome young man and has his finger on the heartbeat of the market so we decided to list. We listed aggressively as he suggested and this fetched us multiple offers with our property going 80k over asking!! What a beauty! This was only one experience with Brandon. The second experience is a single family home in Montecito burnaby. I had fully renovated. Brandon showed up and fell in love with the place. I told Brandon  do you think we can get $2.5  we had purchased 1.5 years prior for $1.840 he said yeah l let s try! I believed that if anyone could fetch this number it would be him. Brandon was a true professional from start to finish and is one of those rare breeds of people who actually does what he says he will. Not some of the time, but all of the time. And is humble and down to earth to boot. With an infectious, positive attitude, and fun to do business with. Brandon follows up leads on his website in a timely manner (to get your business, a good start), comes fully prepared to buyer or seller meet and greet meetings, and I found him to have excellent knowledge of current market conditions and current market selling prices. He uses good professionals (such as photographers), manages the showings and sales processes professionally, and closes win-win deals. In my case as a seller, we had three full price offers within a week (in the slow period of Nov 16-30 just before Christmas 2021), that all fell through for various reasons (financing turned down, etc). Not to worry, we got a fourth full price offer, and that sealed the deal. I enjoyed working with Brandon, and found him to be a true professional, and I would highly recommend him to any friends or associates, or others just looking for a good broker, on either the buying or selling side. My experience with Brandon was first class, 10/10, with no reservations.

During the offer stage, he was very thoughtful and knowledgeable, using the right strategies and tactics to present offers with fair negotiation that allowed us to get our dream unit BELOW the asking price, and this is all because of Brandon s experience in this hot market. The crazy thing about this is that the place was 20 meters away from my location. Feeling like a kid from a candy shop,  I had the choices of different type of ice I wanted. They explained to me the best type of ice to use cause I told them I was going camping. Using a block of ice to keep your food or beverage cold in a cooler goes goes way further than getting ice cubes on a bag. Found that out quickly when I was at the camp ground and that fellow friends ice were already melting and their coolers were filled with water. Very appreciated from their tips and the price of ice is a  way better deal than any local stores. They just deal with ice and the people or business that need it. Quick and simple. Know now and my friends where to go .

However I did get a call the morning of my appointment to check I was coming in and the staff were friendly. I had a really good experience with Dr Mark Abbey, as a foreigner in Vancouver without my own Dr here it s always hit and miss with a walk in clinic. I found Dr Abbey was friendly and actually listened to why I was there rather than pushing me out the door moments after arriving which is how I feel most of the time seeing Drs in this city. It was nice to feel like a person not a number (:

detailed_reviews.review_text: Walked in to this clinic several months ago after seeing a doctor elsewhere (that told me I had a bad cold and prescribed me cough syrup with codeine). I was sick for weeks and couldnt breathe and was staying up all night with a rattle in my chest. Walked in to this clinic, was seen right away with no wait time at all, and explained my situation to the doctor. She didnt say much, which at first I thought was off-putting, but I quickly realised she was doing her job properly and professionally. She assessed me, told me I had bronchitis and that I had gotten much worse since the other Dr. at another clinic had misdiagnosed my symptoms. She quickly prescribed me some antibiotics and an inhaler to help clear my chest. I felt better within a couple of days. If not for her I fear I may have gotten much worse. 10/10 would recommend this clinic, as the staff are competent and understanding. They arent customer service representatives, they are health-care professionals, and thats what I want when I see a doctor.

Dr Gillian Fisher and receptionist Nina are brusque, highly competent, kind, overworked, helpful, and professional. If Dr Fisher had her own practice, Id have her as my own doctor in a heartbeat. Dr Roger Dickey and other doctors Ive seen here have also been great. The wait gets longer as the day progresses, and sometimes the last hour or two are already full by mid-afternoon, just like all walk-in clinics in the neighbourhood. I recommend going as early as you can, or plan to go to the park or do errands nearby.
Dr Amir is by far the best doctor Ive ever went too, hes knowledgeable & fast and helpful. The receptionist are amazing too!

I love this walk-in clinic. Ive never had to wait. The doctors aways listen to me. I dont understand why its rated so low. I always come here when my family doctor is too busy and booked far in advance. IF I could get my family doctor here, I would! Seriously, check it out!

Doctor was amazing. There was a long wait, but that depends on when you go and how busy it is. It is after all a walk in clinic. And the doctor spent a full 25 minutes with me because I was a complicated case. And I appreciated what she did, I walked out with much fewer worries , and she made sure I got the tests I needed. I have always liked Dr. Fisher and the receptionist but it is not being managed well at all right now, causing dire circumstances in many patients life.

Very poorly managed. They forgot to send my specialist referral two times and they never take accountability for their mistake. The phone visit from the physician was fine but dealing with their admin people is a nightmare. They rarely answer the phone and their voicemail is always full.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello Farzod, thank you for taking the time to leave your rating. Could you please get in contact with us directly? We would like to find out a little bit more about what occurred during your most recent visit to our clinic. Thank you. Clinic Support Office: commercialdrivemedicalclinic@gmail.com

detailed_reviews.review_text: Receptionist was literally eating pizza at the desk. lmao Half way home, I get a phone call from her saying she forgot to give me my doctors note so I had to go back. The place is super outdated and reeked of cigs.. This place needs an upgrade too. After I left, I felt super dirty and gross. I had to shower right away.
The skin treatment services here are kinda shady .They seem to be operating without a license o_o
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Dear Elin, thank you for taking the time to leave your rating. All of our doctors are licensed physician. Could you please get in contact with us directly? We would like to find out a little bit more about what occurred during your most recent visit to our clinic. Thank you. Clinic Support Office: commercialdrivemedicalclinic@gmail.com

detailed_reviews.review_text: Possibly the most unreliable clinic in the city. The front desk, please  Get a new job and hire a donkey to work for you instead, it will do a far better job than you can ever.

I don t know what is going on with this business? I was going here and seeing a doctor. I had my medical exam for my professional license and then got a requisition for some lab tests. After months of waiting the doctor never explained the results and when I call the office ( nearly impossible to get through) a young man promised me that a doctor would call me back at 2pm that day. I suspected I wouldn t get a call and sure enough no response after months of trying to get ahold of the doctor and office staff. What a completely incompetent, unprofessional and irresponsible business! Don t use this walk in clinic it s a joke!

Avoid this place for gods sake. A bunch of liars. They told us three (!!!) times month after month that signed us up to MRI queue while they never actually did it. They told us that they CANT TELL US WHICH PARTICULAR CLINIC WE ARE ASSIGNED TO. They cant. Ofc you cant if you never did it. Liars. Stupid, arrogant. Hope you guys have 0 working days week instead of 2. You didnt deserve a penny from MSP. How dare you to make a human suffer for a half a year from backpain and be afraid to tell you simply lied. P.S. to the owner: check my email which I sent on Mar 18, 2023, 3:06 PM asking about MRI date. Which you never bothered to respond ofc.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Dear Omar, thank you for taking the time to leave your concern. Can you contact us directly at commercialdrivemedicalclinic@gmail.com. Currently by checking your last name, we have no record of you being in our clinic, there are multiple clinics in commercial drive location. We look forward to getting your email and will look into this further.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Made an appointment 3 weeks ago online. Never received a confirmation or a phone call to confirm, so I took it upon myself to do that. To my surprise, no one answers the phone or checks their voice mails, so its incredibly difficult to get ahold of anyone to confirm. Arrived on a separate scheduled date and time, and was told to come back in an hour because the doctor was going on break. I already rearranged my day to accommodate this medical appointment, so why cant anyone from this office call me to do the same? Overall the staff are unprofessional and inconsiderate of clients. Improvements severely needed.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you for taking the time to leave your rating and concern. Could you please get in contact with us directly? I would like to find out a little bit more about what occurred during your most recent visit to our clinic. Thank you. Clinic Owner Office: commercialdrivemedicalclinic@gmail.com

detailed_reviews.review_text: Terrible experience. I walked in with a requisition. All I needed was a self-administered swab tube.  Receptionist said they couldn t fit me in with a doctor. I don t need a doctor, I repeated several times. I just needed a tube for a self-administered test. They said I needed a requisition. I already have a requisition. They take it, grab a tube for me. Tell me I can t use their bathroom to do the self test, I would have to go somewhere else. I literally walk to the walk-in clinic next door who were more than happy to let me use their washroom to complete the test. I go to drop off the tube at LifeLabs, only to find they have given me the wrong tube. Great. EDIT: In response to the reply - new and training is one thing, but this receptionist was dismissive and patronizing. I had a simple request, and she made the interaction frustrating and I left in disbelief, unsure of what I had done to make her so angry with me.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Dear Chelsey, Thank you for taking the time to leave your concerns. We apologies that you had a bad experience here. Both of our staff are new and they are on training, we will do our best to speed them up. We have tried to contact you multiple time regarding this issue.

detailed_reviews.review_text: I called in this morning to make an appointment for a botox consultation and the receptionist told me I had to come in right at that moment as there is no one waiting and they dont do appointments. Given that I work about 10 mins away, I arrived approx 20 mins after the phone call and had to wait another  8-10 mins while the receptionist was on the phone with no acknowledgement. After she took my ID and set me up, I asked  her how long it will take for someone to meet me and she tells me that the doctor has gone on break and wont be back for another at least 30 mins and that there is someone else in front of me. I have no issue waiting my turn and am not upset by this at all. That was completely fair, I saw the women ahead of me waiting before I got there. When I tell the receptionist that I was under the impression there was no wait given what she had told me on the phone, she told me that since the doctor saw no one was there, he went on break. I am not saying that the doctor does not deserve a break but at least schedule the breaks or close the clinic for the 30 mins - 1 hour that break takes place. I have seen many clinics use this method and it works best. My issue is not with the doctor but the incompetent receptionist, given my friends experience, I will come by again for a consultation and we will see if this is an overall staff problem.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Dear Stella, thank you for taking the time to leave your rating and concern. Could you please get in contact with us directly? I would like to find out a little bit more about what occurred during your most recent visit to our clinic. Thank you. Clinic Owner Office: commercialdrivemedicalclinic@gmail.com

detailed_reviews.review_text: This office is so disrespectful they told me a doctor would call me and it s been two days they have not called me. They need to find a new solution where they can accommodate everybody s needs. I m very unhappy and disappointed at this.

The initial appointment went fine but the follow up did not. The receptionist offered me a 10 am call two days later to review my X ray results but they never called. I wasn t able to reach them by phone or email. No effort was made to follow up with me on my results.

Accidentally deleted my earlier review when trying to update it. That one was basically went to the doctor with a problem, doctor gave useless advice to which I told him Id tried that for a week and I needed him to help he responded telling me I hadnt done it. Basically on go here if youre about to die and have no other options. The staff,  both reception and medical are awful and wont help with anything. The update was going to be I needed a form signed by a doctor, just a signature. Turns out this walk in clinic no longer has a doctor so its just a useless building with a rude receptionist wholl take all your details before telling you that theres no doctor and wont be for at least a month. No reason to ever go here.

Receptionist ignored my phone calls and when I asked her why she said she got my messages but didn t feel like responding.  Then she said she didn t get them because her phone wasn t working right, then she said she didn t get them because her computer and printer were not working.  I called 9 times today, left various messages on more than one day and received no response.  She hung up on me, said she owns the place, said she doesn t have to respond to calls she doesn t want to, and interrupts patients.  Very unprofessional ever since the pandemic.  I have been going here for 10 years or so and was treated like garbage.

I came to see a doctor, the woman at reception ignored me standing outside for about 5 mins even though it was during their hours of operation. Eventually she answered the door and told me they re doing phone consultations only - then please update your website to clearly state this because right now you re misleading people who need to see a doctor in person.

Signed up and confirmed an online virtual appointment over 1 week ago and never got the call at the scheduled time or any further contact of any kind. Clearly incompetent. First impressions are everything so obviously I will never attempt to go back here for any reason. If they call right now Ill tell them they are trash and hang up......but they wont call lol
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello Light, thank you for taking the time to leave your rating. Could you please get in contact with us directly? We would like to find out a little bit more about what occurred during your most recent visit to our clinic. Thank you. Clinic Support Office: commercialdrivemedicalclinic@gmail.com

detailed_reviews.review_text: I originally came here because they update their times on medimap and I saw that they consistently had short wait times. I loved the doctor I saw the first time, and have been back twice since. However, the receptionist ruins the experience and the way that the clinic runs makes it impossible to give this place a good rating. Their times listed are absolutely inaccurate. For example I was there today at 8:50am expecting the clinic to open at 9am. On the door they have no times posted, only online. The clinic finally opened at 9:30am. I walked in and the receptionist said they were not open for walk-ins as no doctors would be in today. I asked why that was not at least posted on the door, she replied theres nothing I can do. I told her that she could post something, even a piece of paper on the door with that information, or update their voicemail (of which they have none) Well at this point Ive taken the day off work, I still need to see a doctor, and all of the clinics are at least an hour wait time. I highly recommend staying away from this place.

name: BLK BOX GYM - Personal Trainer in Richmond BC

owner.name: BLK BOX GYM - Personal Trainer in Richmond BC (Owner)

address: BLK BOX GYM - Personal Trainer in Richmond BC, 2188 No 5 Rd, Richmond, BC V6X 2T1

detailed_reviews.review_text: If you are looking for a CHANGE or NEED someone to give you motivation to work out, BLK Box gym is where you should head to right now. Friendly staff, clean and well organized gym with lots of equipments I have been trained by many personal trainers in my life but after meeting Ken, my new personal trainer, I have realized not all the trainers are the same. He really puts in effort and care towards his clients, very well organized, uses his experience and knowledge to help his clients reach their goals. Any trainers can push you to work out and do cardios, but Ken actually makes perfect work out/diet plans for each individual Highly recommended 10/10

I joined BLK box gym because I wanted to lose some weight for my graduation ceremony. My experience has been nothing but great. Everyone at the gym was kind and helpful especially my lovely trainer, Rachel. Rachel was tough at times, I used to call her evil, and very caring and attentive on the days I was feeling down. I enjoyed training with Rachel, I enjoyed the music she used to play for my sessions and I was very happy with the transformation I saw on my body after only 2 months of training. Also, I appreciate how Rachel was very understanding of my busy schedule and how she used to push me to keep coming to the sessions regularly. I am very happy with the results I achieved in the 6 months of training with Rachel and I would ve continued working with her if I didn t have to move out of town. All the best Rachel :)
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Fatima, Thank you for your kind review! Were really happy to hear how Rachel made an impact in your fitness lifestyle :)

detailed_reviews.review_text: Ive been training with David for a few months and he changed my body in just 1 month. I was stunned to see how far I had come in such little time. I have known David for several years and his energy is infectious. I dealt with bloating, hypothyroidism and iron deficiency while doing shift work which all lead to a decline in my health. I went from almost 130lbs of skinny fat to 114lbs of muscle. He has helped me obtain the physique Ive always wanted and the strength I never knew that I had. He s incredibly attentive, knowledgeable, and an overall genuine trainer and boxing coach.  His positive attitude and approachable nature makes me feel completely at ease. I cannot recommend David enough as he truly knows what he is doing and you will see how he genuinely cares about your goals. He radiates passion and dedication for his clients and I absolutely love training with him. He will make you succeed with your fitness goals. If youre seeking a trainer who will produce results and make you enjoy it at the same time - you have found the right place. My only regret is not starting with him sooner. I am so incredibly happy - Thank you David and the amazing Blk Box Team

I ve been working with Dave Rojo for personal training sessions since March and can t say enough positive things about the experience. He s always motivating and brings a super fun energy to each session (along with a furry friend, Obie, who is a ray of sunshine). I feel stronger than ever and it s great to be able to just show up and have an entire workout planned for you, along with the encouragement to push yourself.

I ve been training at BLK BOX for 5 months now. Initially I came because I was experiencing back pain and in general was not happy with my body and mindset (COVID greatly affected me). I was reeeally nervous because I had never trained in the gym before and avoided physical exertion in every possible way It s been five months - I ve never felt like skipping a workout. My PT Preston is incredibly professional, knowledgeable and supportive. Going to train with him and seeing the rest of the team is always the highlight of my day. I feel so much better both physically and mentally. Can t recommend this place enough!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Ecstatic to hear you enjoy training with Preston, Sofia! Really proud of your hard work and discipline in the last 5 months   keep killing it!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Just completed 36 personal training sessions with Ken, he is very kind, patient, and professional! I m happy that Ken helped me develop a healthier life style! Every staff is friendly! If you are looking for personalized training plan, BLK is definitely a great choice.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Were happy you had a blast training with Ken, Mavis! Thank you for your kind words, were glad that youre satisfied with your time at BLK BOX GYM.

detailed_reviews.review_text: The slogan  weight lost  is exaggerated in most places but if you re looking for real results then you need to go to Blk Box. I trained for two years prior to Blk Box at commercial gyms and I noticed little chances to my body. The tailored program at Blk Box actually made a difference and I could see how my body changed every single week; not to mention what a pleasure it was to work with Ken. He s extremely knowledgeable you can ask him anything training related and he would be able to answer you. He even helped me recovered from an old injury that prevented me from doing many of the movements. Every single trainer at the gym is friendly and has his/her own personality that you can fell in love with. His rate is also very reasonable comparing to other personal trainers. I m excited to see how Blk Box continues to grow!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hey Allen! Thank you for leaving your kind review for us. Were really happy that you had a great time working with Ken.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Rachel is my personal trainer and is fantastic. Very easy to talk to, pushing me even when I want to give up and flexible with my crazy schedule. So happy with my results so far and will definitely be continuing with her in the future!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Kyo, Thank you for sharing your kind words! Were happy that Rachel helped you with the results that you wanted!

detailed_reviews.review_text: I originally reached out to BLKBOX in Richmond because I had fitness aspirations but didnt know where to begin. Harris (my trainer) was incredibly knowledgable and friendly, and we got to know each other quite well over the several months that I trained there. Harris helped me understand that lifting wasnt just about heavy weights, and he was great at explaining how mobility, rest and nutrition played such a significant part in it as well. Though my time at BLKBOX has wrapped, Im really fortunate to be able to call Harris a good friend of mine now. One of my favourite things about BLKBOX is how I got to know all the other trainers as well. Its a really tight-knit team that are all super fun to be around and they dont make you feel intimidated or self-conscious to be there. Its a great community and I definitely miss being around that team on a weekly basis, and I would definitely reach out again if I were to need personal training once again!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you Caleb! Your radiant energy has been a great addition to our family. We appreciate you!

detailed_reviews.review_text: I have been training in BLK Box gym more than a year. My trainer Matt is the most professional trainer I have ever met. I started training with rare experience and he taught me a lot knowledge about weight lifting and nutrition. And at the most of time his motivation encourage me to work harder and helped me to reach the goal. The space is clean and every single trainer is friendly. I feel so welcomed every time when I go there. I highly recommend this gym if you are looking for a personal training program.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you, Yinan! Were happy to hear that youve enjoyed your experience with Matt.

detailed_reviews.review_text: BLK box gym provides great experience with the thorough sessions of personal training! Had Ken as my trainer and he was knowledgeable and nice to work with. Would definitely recommend BLK box gym for professional training sessions.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello Edward! Were happy to hear that your training with Ken has been a great journey! Ken and the rest of the team appreciate you leaving a review for us :)

detailed_reviews.review_text: Personal training with Ken at BLK Box Gym surpassed all of my previous training experiences at any other corporate gym. BLK Box s environment is clean and the facilities are top notch as well. It is definitely a gym that I would recommend to anyone looking to progress in fitness/lifting journey through their detailed personal training programs.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Jason! Thank you for leaving us a review! We really appreciate your kind words and happy to hear that Ken has provided you an excellent time at BLK BOX :)

detailed_reviews.review_text: I have had the pleasure of training with Jodie for the past several months; she has been an outstanding trainer. Jodie is highly knowledgeable and well-versed in human anatomy. She integrates her knowledge of anatomy and physiology into our sessions, making them educational and insightful. Jodie created various workout split programs for me and she kept me accountable and on track with my fitness goals. She is a kind, sweet and attentive trainer that tailors your workout to your needs while keeping up the intensity of the sessions. I strongly recommend BLK BOX gym for personal training in Richmond!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much, Lily! Youve been such a great addition to our family here at BLK BOX - come visit soon.

detailed_reviews.review_text: After training at BLK Box for 5 months I have come away with so much love and respect for the culture of this gym. Matt and Ken have created a business that offers not only high calibre of coaching and training in many different fitness-related areas but a friendly atmosphere to train and learn. Shortly after I started all the trainers at the gym greeted me by name when I walked in to my sessions and I soon felt a connection to this community. My trainer, Matt, listened to my goals and created a program that set me up for success and I so enjoyed learning from him and his infectious passion and expertise for bodybuilding and nutrition. I look forward to working with him again in the future! Similarly, in hearing conversations between other clients and trainers it was clear that everyone had each others best interests in mind and were there to be kind and helpful. This is a fantastic premium fitness studio that truly has coaches and trainers for all levels and areas of fitness interest. I cant wait to go back and see the newly renovated facilities and continue to support this business!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your kind words, Jake! Its been such a thrill to have you around and apart of our family. Were looking forward to your return!

detailed_reviews.review_text: after 2 sessions of personal training with ken, i got great tips on my form and an extensive plan for my nutrition and split, everyone was very friendly as well.

My personal training experience has been by far one of the best experiences I have experienced at BLK BOX GYM in Richmond.
