I like dr Vasquez so much that when i was thinking about moving away, i considered the fact that Id be losing him as my dr. Spoiler alert, im still here. The front staff are also very lovely, always polite, compassionate and Very professional. I honestly cant understand anyone having an issue with this clinic. Lynne LeBlanc Update: I moved to the sunshine Coast and take the ferry over anytime I need to see Dr. Vasquez. Good doctors are really hard to come by, So when you find a Dr like him, trust me you dont give him up easily.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your kind words Lynne!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Dr. Cubra is the best doctor I ve seen so far. He listens very well, and answers all your questions before your mind even thinks of asking them. I never feel rushed with him. The staff is nice and I never have to wait for my appointment.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you Sasha!

detailed_reviews.review_text: It was a week before Christmas, and I had a horrible throat infection/flu. EVery single clinic in Richmond was full till AFTER boxing day. I was loosing hope. Then my brother in-law called this clinic. They told him the wait was 45 mins. When I got to the clinic I indeed waiting 45 mins, then quickly got brought back to the exam room. This sweet lady doctor walked in and she was so nice, listened to me then checked me out I was in and out within 10-15mins.eill deffinatly be coming back
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Glad we could accommodate you Michelle!  Hope youre well.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Best clinic I have ever been too. It is very difficult to find doctors who genuinely take the time to listen and analyze and take care of their patients. I have followed these drs from their previous clinic, now to this one, because I know I am in good hands with them.

Great staff and doctors who genuinely care. Dr. Vasquez has been our family doctor in Burnaby, and when he moved farther to this clinic, we followed. Great views inside the clinic that overlook the Fraser River.
Dr. Vasquez is an amazing caring doctor . He works at seeing you on short notice as well as your set apptmt. Thrilled to call him my family doctor .

detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Alexander, Perhaps there was some confusion on your part about how our earlier exchanges transpired, so please allow me to provide some clarity. You initially requested a weekend appointment a few months ago, and we were, unfortunately, unable to accommodate your ask as it fell outside our hours of operation. I did, however, still help you the best I could by locating another clinic near you as an alternative. Your request and my subsequent email correspondences occurred during a brief period when we experienced difficulties with our email server, something for which I apologized for at the time. As I am sure you know, it is an unfortunate reality that technology does not always work the way we expect it should despite our best efforts. When you spoke with my colleague last week requesting an appointment, she informed you of our clinic policy which requires new patients to present to the clinic by walk-in for their first visit. I am afraid you may have confused these two different exchanges, which occurred nearly eight months apart, as one occurrence, one of which was not your own. Nevertheless, I feel it is important to offer insight into any misconceptions you may still have about how a medical clinic, specifically our clinic, operates so that you are better informed in the future when trying to access care. The foundation of a walk-in clinic operates on the principle that a patient may present to a clinic without an appointment to access urgent or time-sensitive medical care on the same day. This concept will cease to exist in its practical sense if there is an expectation that clinics should schedule appointments in advance. Moreover, scheduling appointments ahead of time in a walk-in setting will make it extremely difficult for patients in need of urgent care to receive timely care. With that said, we also recognize that,  for a number of people, an appointment system is more ideal due to personal or professional commitments. For this reason, we operate as a hybrid by offering both walk-in and appointment services so that we may better accommodate everyone. To ensure we can accomplish this successfully, a number of different policies have had to be implemented to organize how and when each service can be rendered. One such policy is that new patients are required to present to the clinic by walk-in for their first appointment. This allows us to validate a new patients information, and ensure they are adequately informed of our clinic policies. While we acknowledge that not everyone will be agreeable to this caveat, it has ultimately allowed us to increase access to care for patients by drastically reducing our no-show rate so we may use resources, such as physician time, more efficiently. Therefore, although we are a business and some of our policies may not always equate to good business acumen, we feel it would be unethical to compromise the quality of care and access to medical services by operating as though healthcare is about commerce rather than the health and well-being of people. I hope the information above can help you understand the events that lead up to your experience, but should you need further clarification for our clinic procedures, I would be happy to address your concerns, so please do not hesitate to contact me. Kind regards, Marjan Amiri, Management for Marine Gateway Medical Clinic

detailed_reviews.review_text: Dr. Michelle Lin is my moms and my family doctor. She is patient, genuine, punctual, efficient, and goes the extra mile to ensure we clearly understand the issues and applicable next steps. We sincerely feel privileged to have her as our family doctor as she always makes sure we are comfortable and well-cared for. For example, Dr. Lin is mindful of slowing down her speech so my mom (English is not her first language) can carefully understand her. She is kind to always ask if we have any further questions before wrapping up our appointment as well. I also had a blood test yesterday and I did not schedule a follow-up appointment. I was pleasantly surprised that Dr. Lin called me today to go through my results together with me! We are both very thankful and appreciative of her wonderful care :)

Dr Currie is great. I recently experienced a loss and was treated in the hospital. Upon getting the records in her office, she went out of her way to personally call me and make sure that I was doing okay mentally. Compared to my previous doctor, wait times arent that bad. The front desk team are friendly and helpful.

Had such a great experience with this office. We havent even met the doctor yet but the receptionists were such a pleasure to interact with.  Went out of their way to try and find our forms and information, which may seem silly but with my previous negative experiences with front desk people, this was a nice change. Office space is nice and the people are warm and friendly. So happy we found this office.

The family doctors at this clinic are exceptional! Hardworking, genuine and go the extra mile. Contrary to some of the other comments, Ive had really positive experiences with the receptionists and MOAs. Theyve been really helpful at coordinating appointments and speedy at letting me know as soon as results come in.

The staff at forward care treat you like family. The doctors pay attention to you and your concerns. Online booking is easy and gets approved quickly. More clinics should strive to be like forward care.

My family Doctor is Venetia Mah.  I trust her and other doctors filling in.  There is free street parking from 930am to 3pm.  Staff here also speak Chinese.  Washroom is clean.  Location is convenient for me.  I can call in the morning to get on the waiting list.
Doctor Yuen is a gem. Shes a real human being with the best of care for all her patients. You wont find a better doctor.
Dr Lam and all her staff are very friendly. I highly recommend a consult with Dr  Lam. They do great work and end up feeling good.
Dr J Wong and the staff at this location are wonderful and treat their patients with great care and attention. Great experience, thank you!
Excellent front desk team and the family doctors are very caring, thank you
Amazing doctors and MOA s!
Excellent doctors.

I chose the Forward Care East Clinic for my mother in law as its close to where she lives, the doctor is caring (Dr Jeffrey Lau) and the reception staff is very efficient. Pre-Covid, when my mother in law had some dizzy episodes on a Saturday, we call the office, they fit her in with another doctor in the office and follow up with a letter to Emergency. Currently, they do either phone appointments or in office appointments and most times when we are in the phone appointment, if the doctor needs to see what is concerning (a rash, take blood pressure, etc.), they do their best to find time to let you come in, luckily for us it was within the same day. They referred my mother in law for a geriatrician, and Dr Zhang is also located in the same office. Very efficient in communication and coordination. Before the Geriatrician appointment, the staff called us twice with reminders. I appreciate the calls and reminders. The online booking is the only negative. We get email notification to book for flu shots, etc but our doctor was not set up, or wont allow on the booking site.  Most times it doesnt work, so best to call the office.

Came in today to get a nasal spray to fight off the seasonal flu. I was surprised that there was no long waiting times and I got my appointment right on time. When I used to see Dr. Chan wait times at the clinic were quite long. Dr. Lau is also a younger asian male doctor around my age so I find it easier to talk to him compared to an old lady or man.

Not a walk in clinic: I typed walk in clinics near me and it pointed me here. I asked the front counter person if I could book an appointment. She said they werent a walk in clinic; that none of the doctors were taking any clients in; I thanked her and left immediately.

To echo a lot of the other reviews, my doctor, Dr. Michelle Lin is fantastic. She is personable, relaxed and is dedicated to finding more than 1 solution to a problem. The issue is with the front desk staff. They exude no compassion or desire to be serving patients. They never make eye contact and speak among themselves (which is totally fine), but on several occasions, they have would cut me off or taken a phone call while I was speaking mid-sentence. Im not sure whether they feel like theyre not valued enough to provide a basic level of customer service, but the level of care between the doctors and receptionists are not comparable.

My family doctor,  Dr. Wu is fantastic, but thats the only reason I go to this clinic. I called to cancel MY appointment, because my daughter stays home with high fever, the receptionist said oh, cancelling the same day appointment will be $30. That was it. No sorry to hear, or any kind words!! Now I have to force myself to go to the clinic, which is full of sick people, with my sick child!  I guess I might as well tell doctor to take a look at her!

The doctors here are all great in my experience, and have a lot of compassion and knowledge.  Dont come if you are shy to work with interns though, as it is a teaching clinic. The front area is not super discreet, or comfortable, and unfortunately I have no relationship with any of the staff: they are not very friendly  or authentic, and never know my name....which makes the overall experience a little impersonal and unpleasant despite the great doctor care.

Both of the doctors Ive seen at this place are fantastic however the staff is TERRIBLE. I lost count of how many referrals have been forgotten, test results that have sat at the front desk without the doctor seeing them before I had to call and make an appointment, them not communicating to the doctor what the appointment was for leading to rescheduling if it required more time than was scheduled for, put on hold for 10+ mins, rude service, etc. Recently I moved to a different city and paid for my childrens medical records to be transferred to our new doctors office. Two weeks later as I was trying to schedule an appt our new doctor said she still hadnt received the records.

The doctors are good but unfortunately I had so many miscommunications with the receptionist on phone. When I got to the clinic the receptionists were dressed up like PJs. Horrible experience but again doctors are nice.

this review is very specific to the older Chinese lady with the frizzy hair girl named Lily, She is very rude and unwilling to help all the time. She seems very unhappy with her role at this clinic. Her behaviour makes unwell people feel worse. Other staff members and Doctors are all exceptional and always willing to go extra mile to help their patients.

I started going to this clinic because my family doctor moved practices. Besides being closer to my home, it is inferior in every way to the old clinic I would go to. The staff, while friendly, are mostly unhelpful and refuse basic things (like calling a taxi for patients). The clinic itself is small and youre forced to make appointments and referrals with 10~ people a couple steps away. Anything you ask the staff or talk to the staff about, everyone will hear. This clinic also doesnt allow you to leave messages outside of clinic hours and doesnt have a voicemail system set up at all, making it impossible to cancel or reschedule appointments if youre sick or outside a normal business hours routine. With the state of healthcare in Vancouver you dont really get much of a choice in where you see a family doctor, but if you do have a choice I would recommend against going to a doctor that works at this clinic.

First I wanna say that I love dr curry. She s amazing and very thorough. This 1 star is for the front staff. THE WORST. When u walk in nobody will greet u when u walk to the counter. It s always a  yes  or something short and rude. Secondly I ve found myself waiting at the front desk waiting to be checked in while the group of girls finish a conversation about what they did on the weekend. Then I had an appointment today in the pm and they ve known since at least 8am they will be closed due to snow but choose to call me from a blocked number an hour before to short cancel my appointment. This appointment has already been moved two times. Lastly, when I called to ask a question about blood work one of the front end girls gave me the wrong information and again two weeks of my time has been wasted. If I wasn t pregnant and in need of a dr I would leave this clinic in a second ONLY based on the worst customer service I ve ever received. That being said I love dr curry. I give her 10/5 stars and will ONLY continue at forward care medical because of her!

doctor is great but the receptionist is horrible! The older asian lady with the short bob hair is always so rude and disrespectful! She shouldnt work there as she looks like she miserable all the time and takes it out on the patients ..both on phone and in person.

The doctor makes you wait an hour or more sometimes but expects you to pay a $50 no show fee for a phone call! A PHONE CALL! (Her hourly wage as a doctor must be $50 x 60 minutes = $3000 per hour). The front desk is useless for the patients.

What is the deal with this clinic? They charge 20 dollars to apply for a doctor and then never call you back? What kind of new scam is this? We have a critical supply of doctors in British Columbia and this clinic is charging for applications in the middle on a pandemic? How is this even legal? TO ANYONE THAT HAS PAID THIS CLINIC MONEY AND HAS NOT BEEN ASSIGNED A DOCTOR, CALL YOUR CREDIT CARD PROVIDER AND CREATE A BACK CHARGE. DO NOT GIVE THESE SCUM BAGS MONEY FOR NOTHING.

Dont ever sign up for any so called Free clinic they offered. If you cancel less than 24 hrs, they will charge you but they dont tell you when you call to sign up. When I called to cancel, the receptionist was very rude and hung up on me. Will never go there again. All the receptionists there should be fired.

0 stars 1. did not obtain consent for a paid procedure 2. also claimed they did not receive my lab results 4 months later just because i went to a location thats different than whats on the requisition form disorganized front desk with the potential to be negligent, avoid if possible
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello Lawrence, we are very sorry about your experiences. If you could email us: info@forwardcaremedical.com with details about your difficulties, we will try our best to help. When patients do not receive their lab results in time, it is usually because of the senders side. With the pandemic, lab results are often delayed due to a high volume in lab report requests. As for the consent for your paid procedure, if you could email or message us with details, we will look into what happened.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Called to make a call and got horrendous service. The receptionist was extremely rude. I would not recommend this clinic.
Forward Care abandons their loyal patients when convenient and nickels and dimes for everything.
This is not a drop in clinic and is not accepting new patients.

I joined the church meetings there for years and really appreciate their passionate heart to serve God and the community. Many volunteers are so committed to serve others by helping in the free classes and programs for the community such as iPad/computer classes for Seniors, family Ukulele classes and many others.
Ive been here ever since I arrived Canada (13 years ago). I love the support and the sense of community that people give. The programs are diverse and suitable for all ages.
I have been coming here for the last 15 years. The people here are friendly, sincere and caring. The programs here are very well organized, diverse and suit the need from 0 - 80!
Church of God in Vancouver is not a building but Gods family which is full of love and care!

detailed_reviews.review_text: A positive, caring rescue that places great attention on finding the right matching homes for each cat they rescue.  Definitely recommend.
People who are in charge of that place are too kind, humble. They take care of helpless creatures by feeding & giving them shelter.

Today I went and got another new kitten from Nikki. I went to her lovely home and met her cat crew. This is my second kitten from her in the last year. Just before Xmas last year my daughter and I got a little ginger girl and we love her so much we wanted to give her a friend.  Of course we went back to Nikki and she didn t let us down. Nikki briefly spoke of how some of these cats as well as dogs,  had been treated prior to her stepping in and rescuing them and about how the pandemic and natural disasters have increased the poor faith of these vulnerable animals.  She really cares for animals.  She is defiantly a cat lady through and through. The work she does for these animals is incredible. I don t know what will happen to all the animals in the b.c in distress when she retires. Although I can t see her retiring bc she cares too much about animals being treated badly. Weather it be an issue of hoarding, owners on substances and or natural disasters. As well as her program for seniors she is right on it. We often get caught up in our busy lives and  forget about animals and there well being.  If you can t adopt a cat from Nikki please consider sponsoring a cat or make a donation. I m not sure if she excepts blankets and towels but that could be an idea as well.
Very passionate and kind. Ive gotten several cats from her and all were well looked after and adjusted well to their new forever home.
Wonderful lady who helped me with my cats.
The lady who runs this establishment really loves the cats. Im happy with how they care for the kitties and ensure they have a happy life.
Much needed - under funded

Awesome organization
That is ok

This program of seniors for seniors is a big scam and financial and emotional  abuse of seniors.  I believed the video which promised to care for the health of the senior cat and all the senior had to do was love the cat.  From the first day Nikki s reluctance to care became evident.  The cat I was looking after was in poor health from the beginning.  Any time I called to get approval to go to the vet, Nikki would shriek at me saying he is  Just an old cat.  I m going to have him euthanized.    The first time she said that, I left the cat at the vets certain he would be killed.  Five days later, the vet called me to pick him up.  I was in SHOCK. Every occasion I had to deal with her was traumatizing and unpleasant!!  A horrible experience.  Abusive. Uses pre-approval to get out of paying.  Stay away from this one. I spent over $3,000 in medical care on my own and she owes me $1500 from pre-approved vet visits which she refuses to pay.  All from the scam that the visits weren t pre-approved.  And how can anyone prove that one way or another? This is cruelty .

detailed_reviews.review_text: Nichola was my physiotherapist after my car accident, and I cannot express enough how important she was to my recovery. Having an in-home therapist was incredibly helpful, and she was cheerful, intelligent, and overall a great therapist. These 5 star ratings are all well-earned. Highly recommended!

I was recently injured in a head on car collision and the damage to my IT Band and left hip joint was so severe I could not walk (my left leg could not support my weight and the pain was excruciating). My lawyer put me in touch with Nichola who came to my home, which was so appreciated and Nichola took care of direct billing ICBC. Nichola has it all. Nichola was excellent at diagnosing my issues (she is a terrific listener) and when it came to doing her magic, each session made significant steps in easing my pains so that I was soon able to walk again. If you are looking for a physiotherapist I recommend you check out Nichola. Shes awesome.

Nichola is the most effective Physio I have ever been treated by.  She treated chronic pain in my neck and after minimal treatments my pain decreased, and my mobility was back to normal.  I highly recommend her for long term pain, quick tune-ups, and anything else that is bother you.

Clover Physio has a handy mobile practice that really helps with my busy schedule. Nichola has a calm and conversational manner that really puts me at ease, as my injuries arent the easiest to work with! She has an array of treatments available - IMS, Massage, Exercises. I always feel better once shes seen me.

Nichola at Clover Physio came directly to my house in Burnaby. I had recently injured myself in a car accident and she dealt with all the ICBC billing with no extra charge to me. I have made a great recovery with the help and guidance from Nichola. The fact she came to my house made such a big difference and she was so kind and helpfull. I would highly recommend Nichola.

I attended Nichola with a pain in my lower back recently and have to say that I was so happy with the service I got at Clover Physio. Nichola was not only very professional but also such a lovely person to work with. I honestly cannot say enough of good things about Nichola and her team. Thanks Nichola for everything xx

Nichola is kind-hearted, very knowledgeable and can identify the root cause of the problem. She takes her time and knows a lot of techniques that have helped with the healing process of a knee surgery. Definitely recommend Nichola!
I went to see Nichola for my neck pain. It was amazing how she knew exactly where the cause of the pain was coming from. She really knows her stuff. After 2 sessions I was pain free. Highly recommend

Amazing approach to treatment! I really like the hands-on approach and appreciate the time and attention Nichola puts in every treatment. Very compassionate, and understanding physio. I highly recommend Nichola!
Nichola is awesome, caring and attentive.  She really helped my back pain that that was incessant for 5 years, now I dont even notice it!

Found Nichola excellent, in diagnosing my problem swiftly and follow up advice concerning exercise, excellent in treatment also. Its up to me to do my part of course, as Nichola says keep doing her advised exercise
Nichola at Clover was an excellent Physio who helped rehab my shoulder so I could continue to play sports, excellent service & very convenient.
An Amazing Physiotherapist Nicola I would highly recommend her my back was giving me so much trouble and after a few sessions Nicola had my back sorted excellent at her job
Nichola really helped me get back to my usual athletic activities quickly after my chronic overuse injuries.
Great physio, I highly recommend Nichola!

detailed_reviews.review_text: The stay was satisfying ) I got access to all the necessary kitchen facilities and other crucial staff needed for a comfortable stay. The Hotels manager is hospital and friendly. The location of the Hotel is in the hurt of Vancouver. Therefore I can recommend this Hotel for long as well as short stays.

Clean, tidy and the bed was quite comfortable. The owner was very nice and helpful. Very nice lady. I did stay  one night with my daughter. This place did satisfy my expectations and I really recommend it for any stay in Vancouver. The kitchen was shared with two other rooms, but me and my daughter had dinner out and left before breakfast. It is close to the sky train, bus, and Oakridge mall is a 7 minute walk. Its also close to a beautiful park. I will definitely be coming back to stay!

The owner Maria was very gracious, friendly  and helpful & made my stay very comfortable. The #1room was very clean and spacious. The shared modern kitchen area came with kitchen gadgets. The location is very near to Oakridge station, mall & supermarket - a walking distance. Returning, for sure
Its clean, the owner is friendly and helpful. I rented a room because I needed a place to study for a whole night and it was super quiet and close to my College.
I may have been lucky, but I stayed in a room with a separate bathroom, the skytrain was nearby, and I was very satisfied with the atmosphere of the surrounding residential areas and parks.

Ive only been here for a couple hrs... Had a nice shower and relaxing on a comfortable bed in my normal sized bedroom. Lots of closet space, a heater, snacks, waters, a large window, extra plug-ins with a power bar, hangers and shelves, blinds and curtains if ya want it dark! Theres a desk to work at if needed, two lamps and ceiling light! So far, so good! Will prolly sleep good tonite!!

Like many I missed the shared bathroom feature on the Hotels.com site, but looking beyond that the host is very welcoming and the place is kept immaculately clean. Even my single room was spacious enough. The kitchenette comes well equipped with hob, fridge and microwave. Crockery and cutlery is also supplied. Theres also a common kitchen upstairs. A TV in the room would have been preferred. If you are a pedestrian then location could be a challenge.  Like many areas of Vancouver redevelopment is killing the local stores and supermarkets so you need to travel further. A 10 minute walk takes you to excellent transit options. A car would open up even more choice. Not remotely accessible due to being an older home.

Maria and staff are so helpful and accommodating ...Very good location ..close to sky train station and bus stop a very short walk ..also close to airport... Room and house are very clean and kitchen facilities are good .
Cozy  bedrooms in Oakridge

detailed_reviews.review_text: We hired pretty in pink management to tend bar at our wedding this past weekend and it was Andrea. We had a terrible experience. I hope no other bride has to deal with this company. First, she showed up late even though we had discussed her arriving early to set up before the wedding reception. We had a line up of people at the bar with no bartender before she even arrived. She also said she was arriving with a complete bar set up with cups and martini shakers as our signature drink was a martini. Andrea did not bring nearly enough cups to the event and was telling guests to keep their plastic cups. She was free pouring all the martinis and was not even using all the ingredients that were laid out for her. The biggest issue we had was we agreed on either a prepaid tip in advance or a tip jar. We decided on a prepaid tip from us so our wedding guests would not have to tip. Andrea asked us how she would approach guests who wanted to tip her anyways. We simply told her to tell guests that the bride and groom were taking care of gratuity. This is not uncommon at all with weddings, and was already agreed upon in an email that we would pay the tip in advance. She then took tips throughout the night and ended up leaving with a large tip jar including multiple bills.. we had a toonie bar. I can t help but assume she took money from our cash made from the bar and helped herself. I am only writing this review because this was one of the most important days of our lives and we feel so taken advantage of. Such unprofessional and shady service and I hope no other bride has to deal with this company or wage their money on this terrible experience. I asked for my original tip back and was ignored. I hope other brides read this and DO NOT HIRE this company.
